# Prepaid MRR

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'Description:'}) %>
Prepaid MRR is the total recurring revenue you have collected from customers,
but haven't provided the service for yet.
<br><br>
Prepaid MRR is the money you'd have to pay back if all your annual subscribers
would cancel and request a full refund for the months they haven't used yet.
<%= partial 'cheat_column_end' %>

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'Use:'}) %>
Estimate the upcoming cost to serve annual subscribers.
<%= partial 'cheat_column_end' %>

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'Target:'}) %>
Having customers in long-term plans is a good thing, so you'll want the prepaid MRR to be as high as possible.
